 Strategies - Kimmeridge Energy                Menu      About UsResearchStrategiesProjectsIn the NewsContact UsPrivate Login    Strategies Private Equity FundsKimmeridge believes that investing in the energy space should be driven by fundamental skills and knowledge. In our view, opportunities in the sector can be broadly subdivided into four themes:GeologyNew geological provinces continue to open up. First movers who identify these early can create considerable value through low-cost leasing.TechnologyThe application of new technology to old fields continues to create new unconventional resource plays, while improving recovery from mature fields. The rapid evolution of technology has created a knowledge gap which is especially pronounced in early-stage plays.CommodityOperators often underestimate the cyclical nature of the commodity markets and believe above or below normal returns will exist for extended periods of time. This creates windows for opportunistic investors to capture mispriced assets.Shareholder Structure ArbitragePublic companies continue to be driven by reserve and production growth. This can create opportunities for private entities to acquire declining assets with high returns and material long term option value at attractive prices.       
 Paradox Basin - Kimmeridge Energy               Menu      About UsResearchStrategiesProjectsIn the NewsContact UsPrivate Login    Paradox BasinKimmeridge farmed into 43,000 net acres in the Paradox Basin in 2013, focused on the liquid-rich portion of the Gothic and Hovenweep Shales. Since the initial entry, Kimmeridge has added a further 16,000 net acres organically, while participating in 6 vertical data gathering wells, several of which have been brought on to production from conventional reservoir targets and appear to confirm Kimmeridge’s geological thesis on the horizontal potential of the play. With the data from the initial test wells encouraging, Kimmeridge has begun the permitting process for a horizontal test.       
